<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1763">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/204.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Discreetly inform Panaman Government that Department’s approval of loan
                            based on hypothecation of income of six million dollars permanently
                            invested in New York, was based on the understanding that this money
                            would be used only for building railroads in Province of Chiriquí.</p>
                        <p>Continue to keep Department fully informed and report by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>